Job Summary
Looking for an exciting opportunity? We are looking for a experienced .NET professionals to be involved in open innovations prototyping, proof of concepts and content discovery projects for our client.
Mandatory Skill-set
Degree in Information Technology, Computer Engineering and / or Computer Science;
At least 5 years' experience in application development, operational support and maintenance;
Experience with container technology like Docker, Docker Swarm or Kubernetes;
Must have experience and certification in AWS;
Technical experience in C# .NET, PHP, PERL, or C++ and front-end technologies like HTML5, jQuery, JavaScript and CSS;
Exposure to with front-end framework like Angular, AngularJS, REACT;
Hands-on in optimized SQL queries or stored procedures;
Working experience in Service Oriented Architecture (SOA) and having integrating application using SOAP or REST services;
Ability to communicate and present technical information in a clear and unambiguous manner;
Strong... ability to work independently and cooperate with diverse teams in a multiple stakeholders environment.
Desired Skill-set
Microsoft Azure Certification;
Google Cloud Certification.
Responsibilities
Responsible for all systems enhancements, support and overall availability of the systems;
Ensure that all production emergencies, issues are resolved in a timely manner based on SLA;
Perform routine checks and escalate to management of any anomaly detected and take initiative to troubleshoot together with various teams and vendors;
Ensure follow through on every issue / problem till closure; and complete the necessary documentation as required;
Assist users and answer queries regarding the supported operational systems;
Ensure necessary changes / enhancements are implemented and documented as per corporate standards and guidelines;
Develop new applications and maintenance of any existing systems assigned;
Ensure projects timeline and resources are tracked.
